P01-01.Name: Control mode setting
P01-01.Instruction:
Set range: 0-6
0: position control mode
1: speed control mode
2: torque control mode
3: speed and torque control mode. You need to use an external input port in CN1 for switching, and set the selected DI port input port function selection to 5 (control mode switching). Controlling the logical state of the port can switch the control mode.
Terminal effective speed mode
Terminal invalid torque mode
4: position and speed control mode. You need to use an external input port in CN1 for switching, and set the selected DI port input port function selection to 5 (control mode switching). Controlling the logical state of the port can switch the control mode.
Terminal effective position mode
Terminal invalid speed mode
5: position and torque control mode. You need to use an external input port in CN1 for switching, and set the selected DI port input port function selection to 5 (control mode switching). Controlling the logical state of the port can switch the control mode.
Terminal effective position mode
Terminal invalid torque mode
6: full closed loop

P01-02.Name: Real time automatic adjustment mode
P01-02.Instruction:
Set range: 0-2
0: manually adjust rigidity.
1: standard mode automatically adjusts rigidity. In this mode, the parameters P02-00, P02-01, P02-10, P02-11, P02-13, P02-14, P08-20 will be set automatically according to the rigidity level set by P01-03, and manual adjustment of these parameters will not work. The following parameters are set by the user:
P02-03 (speed feed forward gain), P02-04 (speed feed forward smoothing constant).
2: positioning mode automatically adjusts rigidity. In this mode, the parameters P02-00, P02-01, P02-10, P02-11, P02-13, P02-14, P08-20 will be set automatically according to the rigidity level set by P01-03, and manual adjustment of these parameters will not work. The following parameters will be fixed values and cannot be changed.
P02-03 (speed feed forward gain): 30%
P02-04 (speed feed forward smoothing constant): 0.50
3: Automatically adjust the rigidity 2, in this mode, the parameters P02-00, P02-01, P02-10, P02-11, P02-13, will be set automatically according to the rigidity level set by P01-03, P08-20 will be set automatically according to the load inertia set by P01-04, P02-14 set value is 100, manual adjustment of these parameters will not work. The following parameters are set by the user:
P02-03 (speed feed forward gain), P02-04 (speed feed forward smoothing constant).

P01-03.Name: Real time automatic adjustment of rigidity setting
P01-03.Instruction:
Set range: 0-31
Built in 32 gain parameters, when P01-02 is set to 1, or 2 time to play a role. It can be called directly according to the actual situation. The greater the setting value, the stronger the rigidity.

P01-04.Name: Moment of inertia ratio
P01-04.Instruction:
Set range: 0-100, unit: times.
Setting the load inertia ratio of the corresponding motor, the setting method is as follows:
P01-04= load inertia / motor moment of inertia
This inertia ratio can be used to write the parameters after the AF-J-L inertia value is recognized.

P01-10.Name: Control mode after overshoot
P01-10.Instruction:
Set range: 0-1
0: after the overpass, the motor is in free state, and only receives the reverse direction signal.
1: after the overpass, the motor is in the locked state, and only receives the reverse direction signal.

P01-20.Name: Dynamic brake delay
P01-20.Instruction:
Set range: 0-150, unit: ms
Action delay time of dynamic brake is satisfied when braking condition is met.

P01-21.Name: No dynamic brake when main power is turned off.
P01-21.Instruction:

0: using dynamic braking
1: turn off dynamic braking.

P01-22.Name: No dynamic brake when servo OFF is used
P01-22.Instruction:

0: using dynamic braking
1: turn off dynamic braking.

P01-23.Name: No dynamic brake when alarming.
P01-23.Instruction:
Set range: 0-1
0: using dynamic braking
1: turn off dynamic braking.

P01-24.Name: No dynamic brake when override.
P01-24.Instruction:
Set range: 0-1
0: using dynamic braking
1: turn off dynamic braking.

P01-30.Name: clasp Brake command - servo OFF delay time (clasp brake opening delay)
P01-30.Instruction:
Set range: 0-255, unit: ms
When enabled: After executing enabled instructions, after the P01-30 time, the driver will receive the position instructions.
When the motor is in a static state, the time from the lock to the non-energized state after the switch-off command is executed.

P01-31.Name: Speed limit value of clasp brake command output
P01-31.Instruction:
Set range: 0-3000, unit: RPM
When the motor is in revolving state, the motor speed threshold of the brake output is effective. Under this threshold, the lock output instruction is valid, otherwise the lock output instruction will be valid after waiting for P01-32 time.

P01-32.Name: Servo OFF clasp brake command waiting time

P01-40.Instruction:
Prevent motor from runaway and abnormal rotation.
0: Guan enables
1: opening and enabling

P02-00.Name: Position control gain 1
P02-00.Description:
Setting range: 0-3000.0, unit: 1/S
The larger the parameter value, the higher the gain ratio, the greater the stiffness, the smaller the position tracking error and the faster the response. However, excessive vibration and overshoot can be caused by excessive parameters.
This parameter is for steady state response.

P02-01.Name: Position control gain 2
P02-01.Description:
Setting range: 0-3000.0, unit: 1/S
The bigger the proportional gain of the position loop regulator, the bigger the parameter value, the higher the gain ratio, the bigger the stiffness, the smaller the position tracking error, and the faster the response. However, excessive vibration and overshoot can be caused by excessive parameters.
This parameter is for dynamic response.

P02-03.Name: Speed feed forward gain
P02-03.Description:
Set range: 0-100.0, unit 1%
The feedforward gain of the speed loop, the larger the parameter value, the smaller the position tracking error of the system, and the faster the response. But the feedforward gain is too large, which makes the position loop of the system unstable and prone to overshoot and vibration.
Set range: 0-100.0, unit 1%
The feedforward gain of the speed loop, the larger the parameter value, the smaller the position tracking error of the system, and the faster the response. But the feedforward gain is too large, which makes the position loop of the system unstable and prone to overshoot and vibration.
Report error

P02-04.Name: Speed feedforward smoothing constant
P02-04.Description:
Setting range: 0-64.00, unit: ms
This parameter is used to set the speed loop feed forward filter time constant. The larger the value, the larger the filtering effect, but the larger the phase lag.

P02-10.Name: Speed proportional gain 1
P02-10.Description:
Setting range: 1.0-2000.0, unit: Hz
The greater the proportional gain of speed, the greater the servo stiffness, the faster the speed response, but too large is easy to produce vibration and noise.
If the system does not generate shocks, try to increase the parameter.
This parameter is for static response.

P02-11.Name: Velocity integral constant 1
P02-11.Description:
Setting range: 1.0-1000.0, unit: ms
The smaller the setting value is, the faster the integrating speed is, the greater the stiffness is, and the smaller the setting value is, the easier vibration and noise will be produced.
When the system does not oscillate, try to reduce the value of this parameter.
This parameter is for steady state response.

P02-12.Name: Pseudo differential feedforward control coefficient 1
P02-12.Description:
Setting range: 0-100.0, unit: 1%
When set to 100.0%, the speed loop adopts PI control, and the dynamic response is fast; when set to 0, the speed loop integral effect is obvious, which can filter low-frequency interference, but the dynamic response is slow.
By adjusting this coefficient, the velocity loop can have better dynamic response and increase the resistance to low frequency interference.

P02-13.Name: Speed proportional gain 2
P02-13.Description:
Setting range: 1.0-2000.0, unit: Hz
The greater the proportional gain of speed, the greater the servo stiffness, the faster the speed response, but too large is easy to produce vibration and noise.
When the system does not generate shocks, try to increase the parameter.
This parameter is for dynamic response.

P02-14.Name: Velocity integral constant 2
P02-14.Description:
Setting range: 1.0-1000.0, unit: ms
The smaller the setting value is, the faster the integrating speed is, the greater the stiffness is, and the smaller the setting value is, the easier vibration and noise will be produced.
When the system does not oscillate, try to reduce the value of this parameter.
This parameter is for dynamic response.

P02-15.Name: Pseudo differential feedforward control coefficient 2
P02-15.Description:
Setting range: 0-100.0, unit: 1%
When set to 100.0%, the speed loop adopts PI control, and the dynamic response is fast; when set to 0, the integral effect of the speed loop is obvious, which can filter low-frequency interference, but the dynamic response is slow.
By adjusting this coefficient, the velocity loop can have better dynamic response and increase the resistance to low frequency interference.

P02-16.Name: Velocity integral error limit amplitude
P02-16.Description: Set range: 0-32767 Speed integral error limit value

P02-19.Name: Torque feedforward gain
P02-19.Description:
Set range: 0-30000, unit: 1%
Set the feedforward weighting value of the current loop. The parameter is weighted by the derivative of the speed instruction, and the current loop is added.

P02-20.Name: Torque feedforward smoothing constant
P02-20.Description:
Setting range: 0-64.00, unit: ms
This parameter is used to set the torque feedforward filter time constant.

P02-30.Name: Gain switching mode
P02-30.Description:
Set range: 0-10
Setting the first and second gain switching conditions
0 fixed as the first gain P02-00, P02-10, P02-11, P02-12
1 fixed second gain P02-01, P02-13, P02-14, P02-15
2 Invalid DI port set to 9 (gain switching input) for DI input switching: First gain is valid: second gain
3 the torque command greater torque command is greater than the threshold (determined by P02-31 and P02-32) when switching to second gain. Less than the threshold, and at the same time exceeding the P02-33 delay setting, switch to the first gain.
4. Switch to the second gain when the change of speed instruction is larger than the threshold (determined by P02-31 and P02-32). Less than the threshold, and at the same time exceeding the P02-33 delay setting, switch to the first gain.
5 speed instruction, large speed instruction is greater than the threshold (determined by P02-31 and P02-32), switching to second gain. Less than the threshold, and at the same time exceeding the P02-33 delay setting, switch to the first gain.
6 position deviation large position deviation greater than the threshold (determined by P02-31 and P02-32) switch to second gain. Less than the threshold, and at the same time exceeding the P02-33 delay setting, switch to the first gain.
7 there is a location instruction that switches to second gain when there is position instruction. When the location instruction ends and the P02-33 delay is set, switch to the first gain.
8 switch to second gain when unfinished positioning is not completed. The location is completed, and at the same time, when the P02-33 delay setting is exceeded, the switch is switched to the first gain.
9 the actual speed is greater than the threshold (determined by P02-31 and P02-32) when switching to second gain. Less than the threshold, and at the same time exceeding the P02-33 delay setting, switch to the first gain.
10 there is a position command + a real speed switch with a position command to second gain. There is no position instruction and the actual speed is less than the threshold (determined by P02-31 and P02-32), and when the P02-33 delay setting is exceeded, the switch to the first gain.

1: speed instruction speed command is less than P02-41 setting threshold is PI control, greater than P control.
2: acceleration acceleration is less than P02-41. When setting threshold is PI control, greater than P control.
The position deviation of 3: is less than P02-41. When setting threshold, PI is the control, and P is the control.

P04-30.Name: 1th Internal setting speed
P04-30.Description: Set range：-6000—6000，Unit：rpm Parameters P04-30 to P04-37 respectively set internal speed 1 to internal speed 8 speed. The internal speed switching method is as follows: When in the speed loop control mode, P04-00 is set at 3. The corresponding input ports are defined as 13, 14, 15. The switching of internal speed is achieved by setting the input port function to 13, 14, 15 on-off state combination. The switching relationship is shown in the below table DI13 DI14 DI15 Action parameters 0 0 0 P04-30 1 0 0 P04-31 0 1 0 P04-32 1 1 0 P04-33 0 0 1 P04-34 1 0 1 P04-35 0 1 1 P04-36 1 1 1 P04-37

P05-00.Name: Torque command source
P05-00.Description:
0: external analog instruction (speed limit amplitude set by P05-02)
1: digital instruction (speed limit amplitude set by P05-02)
2: external analog instruction (speed limit amplitude determined by speed analog instruction).
3: digital instruction (speed limit amplitude determined by speed analog instruction).

P05-01.Name: Torque command analog quantity inverse
P05-01.Description:
Used to adjust torque direction
0: normal
1: direction reversal

P05-02.Name: Torque mode speed limiter set value
P05-02.Description:
Set range: 0- maximum speed, unit: RPM
Setting the maximum speed of motor in torque mode to prevent mechanical damage caused by high speed of motor in no-load condition
Torque control mode effective

P05-05.Name: Torque limiting setting source
P05-05.Description:
Source for adjusting torque limiting amplitude
0: internal digital quantity (set by P05-10, P05-11 or P05-12, P05-13)
1: external analog (T-REF input from external analog input). In this mode, the amplitude of the positive and negative directions is the same.

P05-06.Name: Torque limit detection output delay
P05-06.Description:
Set range: 0-10000, unit: ms
Set DO port output torque limit to detect delay time of output signal.

P05-10.Name: Internal forward torque limiting amplitude
P05-10.Description:
Setting range: 0-300.0, unit: 1%
Limit the positive output of motor, 100 indicates 1 times torque, 300 indicates 3 times torque.
When the torque output reaches the limit value, the output signal can be detected through the output torque limit of the DO port.

P05-11.Name: Internal reverse torque limiting amplitude
P05-11.Description:
Setting range: 0-300.0, unit: 1%
Limit motor reverse output, 100 represents 1 times torque, 300 indicates 3 times torque.
When the torque output reaches the limit value, the output signal can be detected through the output torque limit of the DO port.

P05-12.Name: External positive torque limiting amplitude
P05-12.Description:
Setting range: 0-300.0, unit: 1%
This function needs to be switched using an external input port in CN1, and the selected DI port input port function selection is set to 7 (forward side external torque limit). Controlling the logical state of the port can switch the control mode.
Terminal logic torque limit amplitude
Effective external limiting amplitude P05-12
Invalid internal limiting amplitude P05-10
If the DI function is not allocated, the default torque limit of the system is P05-10.
When the torque output reaches the limit value, the output signal can be detected through the output torque limit of the DO port.

P05-13.Name: External reverse torque limit amplitude
P05-13.Description:
Setting range: 0-300.0, unit: 1%
This function needs to be switched using an external input port in CN1, and the selected DI port input port function selection is set to 8 (Reverse Side External Torque Limit). Controlling the logical state of the port can switch the control mode.
Terminal logic torque limit amplitude
Effective external limiting amplitude P05-13
Invalid internal limiting amplitude P05-11
If the DI function is not allocated, the default torque limit of the system is P05-11.
When the torque output reaches the limit value, the output signal can be detected through the output torque limit of the DO port. Report errors
